        <!-- Section: Catastrophic Risk -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-6">The Catastrophic Risk No One Talks About</h2>
            
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                This is the most important concept a retiree can understand.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                It's called <strong>Sequence of Returns Risk</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                It's a simple concept: <strong>WHEN your returns happen matters more than your <em>average</em> return.</strong>
            </p>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Let's look at two retirees. Both have $1,000,000. Both need to withdraw $50,000 (5%) per year to live.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-4 mb-6">
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span><strong>Retiree A (Traditional 60/40 Plan):</strong> Retires into a bear market.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span><strong>Retiree B (0% Floor Strategy):</strong> Retires into the <em>exact same</em> bear market.</span>
                </li>
            </ul>

