                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 font-bold leading-relaxed mb-6">
                The question isn't about cost—it's about <em>value.</em>
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-6">Who Should Consider Each Strategy?</h3>

            <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-8 border-green-600 rounded-r-lg p-6 my-6 shadow-lg">
                <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4">A Roth IRA May Be Right For You If:</p>
                <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-green-600 font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You have minimal financial liabilities (no mortgage, car loans, or credit card debt)</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-green-600 font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You're single or have no dependents</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-green-600 font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You already have adequate life and disability insurance elsewhere</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-green-600 font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You want the absolute lowest cost structure</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-8 border-myBlue rounded-r-lg p-6 my-6 shadow-lg">
                <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-myBlue mb-4">An IUL May Be Right For You If:</p>
                <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You have significant liabilities: mortgage, auto loans, student debt, or credit card balances</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You have a spouse, children, or aging parents who depend on your income</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You want to protect your family from losing their home if something happens to you</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You live in a state where certain debts can pass to your children or spouse</span>
                    </li>
                    <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                        <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                        <span>You want a comprehensive solution that protects against market loss, critical illness, AND provides a legacy</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-boxGray border-l-8 border-myRed rounded-r-lg p-6 my-8 shadow-lg">
                <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-myRed mb-4">Critical Reality Check:</p>
                <p class="text-xl text-black leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    <strong>Common family liabilities include:</strong> Mortgage debt, auto loans, credit card balances, student loans, medical debt, business obligations, and co-signed loans.
                </p>
                <p class="text-xl text-black leading-relaxed">
                    <strong>In some states</strong>, certain types of debt can legally transfer to surviving family members. If you pass away with outstanding obligations, an IUL's death benefit can prevent your family from inheriting your debt burden—or worse, losing their home.
                </p>
            </div>

            <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                This strategy is for you if:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-none space-y-4 mb-6">
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span>You believe protecting your principal is <em>more</em> important than chasing high-risk gains.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span>You are worried about a market crash wiping out your retirement.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span>You are worried about future tax rates destroying your 401(k) income.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span>You want to protect your family from financial disaster if something happens to you.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="text-xl leading-relaxed flex items-start">
                    <span class="text-myBlue font-bold mr-3">&#9656;</span>
                    <span>You want to sleep at night.</span>
                </li>
